        486.32
      ],
      "block_index": 30,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p164_s0088",
      "text": " If another N_Port ID is currently logged in with the same Port Name as contained in the FDISC request ",
      "bbox": [
        105.94,
        476.65,
        523.26,
        490.3
      ],
      "block_index": 30,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 2
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p164_s0089",
      "text": "payload, or if the Port Name is the same as the Permanent Port Name associated with another N_Port, then ",
      "bbox": [
        112.74,
        491.24,
        541.34,
        501.28
      ],
      "block_index": 30,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p164_s0090",
      "text": "the response should be LS_RJT (Logical error, invalid port name).",
      "bbox": [
        112.74,
        502.28,
        375.0,
        512.32
      ],
      "block_index": 30,
      "line_index": 3,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p164_s0091",
      "text": "b",
      "bbox": [
        101.94,
        513.68,
        105.94,
        521.72
      ],
      "block_index": 30,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p164_s0092",
      "text": " When an FDISC with S_ID=0 is received when no more N_Port_IDs are available, the F_Port shall respond ",
      "bbox": [
        105.94,
        512.05,
        541.27,
        525.7
      ],
      "block_index": 30,
      "line_index": 4,
      "span_index": 2
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p164_s0093",
      "text": "with an LS_RJT with an LS_RJT Reason Code of Unable to perform command request and an LS_RJT ",
      "bbox": [
        112.74,
        526.64,
        525.82,
        536.68
      ],
      "block_index": 30,
      "line_index": 5,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p164_s0094",
      "text": "Reason Code Explanation of insufficient resources.",
      "bbox": [
        112.74,
        537.68,
        316.4,
        547.72
      ],
      "block_index": 30,
      "line_index": 6,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p164_s0095",
      "text": "c",
      "bbox": [
        101.94,
        549.08,
        105.54,
        557.12
      ],
      "block_index": 30,
      "line_index": 7,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p164_s0096",
      "text": " Any assigned N_Port ID may be individually logged out and disassociated with the Permanent Port Name, ",
      "bbox": [
        105.54,
        547.45,
        536.34,
        561.1
      ],
      "block_index": 30,
      "line_index": 7,
      "span_index": 2
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p164_s0097",
      "text": "including the FLOGI-assigned N_Port ID; Name Server attributes for the N_Port ID are cleared. Other ",
      "bbox": [
        112.74,
        562.03,
        518.24,
        572.08
      ],
      "block_index": 30,
      "line_index": 8,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p164_s0098",
      "text": "logged-in N_Port IDs continue to be associated with their current Permanent Port Names. See FC-GS-5 for ",
      "bbox": [
        112.74,
        573.08,
        540.84,
        583.12
      ],
      "block_index": 30,
      "line_index": 9,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p164_s0099",
      "text": "a definition of Permanent Port name.",
      "bbox": [
        112.74,
        584.06,
        259.16,
        594.1
      ],
      "block_index": 30,
      "line_index": 10,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p164_s0100",
      "text": "d",
      "bbox": [
        101.94,
        595.46,
        105.94,
        603.5
      ],
      "block_index": 30,
      "line_index": 11,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p164_s0101",
      "text": " Whenever a new N_Port ID is assigned by either FLOGI or FDISC, or logged out, the nameserver database ",
      "bbox": [
